parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to deaccelerate suddenly, hesitate, or buck, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the electrical system can cause the battery to drain, the alternator to break, and the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the computer system can cause the entire system to shut down, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: and the whole system needs to be replaced.

symptoms: Transmission intermittently slips into different modes
idle speed is too high or too low
engine completely shuts down while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: flames shooting up when the vehicle is stopped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine overheating can cause engine damage, breakdowns, and potentially lead to engine failure.

Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Additionally, related issues with the valves, air conditioning, brakes, and interior components can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
Brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as the vehicle may not be able to stop in time or at all.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn brake pads and faulty rotors can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
